# Environment Configuration

Copy this file to `.env` and update values for your environment.

## Development (Local)

```
# API Configuration
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=8000
API_TITLE=Secure Document & Link Sharing Platform
API_VERSION=1.0.0

# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/document_sharing

# Redis
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-change-in-production-minimum-32-chars
JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=30
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS=7

# File Service
FILE_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:8081

# Java File Service
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/document_sharing
spring.datasource.username=user
spring.datasource.password=password
file.storage.path=/tmp/uploads
```

## Docker Compose

Already configured in `docker-compose.yml`. Services communicate via container network names.

## Railway Production

Set these in Railway dashboard:

```
# API Service
DATABASE_URL=${{Postgres.DATABASE_URL}}
REDIS_URL=${{Redis.REDIS_URL}}
JWT_SECRET=<generate_strong_secret_32_chars_min>
FILE_SERVICE_URL=https://<file-service-url>.up.railway.app
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=$PORT

# File Service
DATABASE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://${{Postgres.PGHOST}}:5432/${{Postgres.PGDATABASE}}?sslmode=require
spring.datasource.username=${{Postgres.PGUSER}}
spring.datasource.password=${{Postgres.PGPASSWORD}}
FILE_STORAGE_PATH=/app/uploads
PORT=$PORT
```

### Generating JWT_SECRET

```bash
# Linux/Mac
openssl rand -base64 32

# Windows
python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
```

## Important Notes

⚠️ **NEVER commit `.env` file to Git** - add to `.gitignore`
⚠️ **Change all default passwords in production**
⚠️ **Use HTTPS in production** - configure with reverse proxy
⚠️ **Rotate secrets regularly**
